.#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.input|xhtml/1.0
.# Verify that an empty line before a macro with non-generated content (editable
.# parameters and/or content rendered in-place) is preserved as an onEmptyLines
.# event at the document level and is not included in the parameter or content
.# value (XRENDERING-806). The difference with emptyline1.test is that the macro
.# here uses data-xwiki-non-generated-content divs, which push new scanner
.# contexts. The fix ensures empty lines are forwarded to the outer context
.# before those new contexts are pushed.
.#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<p>Text</p><div class="wikimodel-emptyline"></div><!--startmacro:info|-|--><div data-xwiki-non-generated-content="java.util.List&lt;org.xwiki.rendering.block.Block&gt;" data-xwiki-parameter-name="title" class="xwiki-metadata-container"><p>my title</p></div><div data-xwiki-non-generated-content="java.util.List&lt;org.xwiki.rendering.block.Block&gt;" class="xwiki-metadata-container"><p>my content</p></div><!--stopmacro-->
.#-----------------------------------------------------
.expect|event/1.0
.#-----------------------------------------------------
beginDocument
beginParagraph
onWord [Text]
endParagraph
onEmptyLines [1]
onMacroStandalone [info] [title=beginDocument [[syntax]=[XHTML 1.0]]
beginParagraph
onWord [my]
onSpace
onWord [title]
endParagraph
endDocument [[syntax]=[XHTML 1.0]]] [beginDocument [[syntax]=[XHTML 1.0]]
beginParagraph
onWord [my]
onSpace
onWord [content]
endParagraph
endDocument [[syntax]=[XHTML 1.0]]]
endDocument
.#-----------------------------------------------------
.expect|xwiki/2.1
.#-----------------------------------------------------
Text


{{info title="my title"}}
my content
{{/info}}
